{"tid":1298783,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"外國媒體:Hong Kong leader says extradition bill is dead","createTime":"2019-07-09T02:39:50.000Z","updateTime":"2019-07-09T04:10:41.000Z","uid":41404,"like":1,"dislike":41,"uniUserReply":10,"replies":[{"pid":"ec1ae786db5e1343a059957c814b0e9393ba3af0","tid":1298783,"uid":41404,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-07-09T02:39:50.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://www.cbc.ca/news/world/hong-kong-extradition-bill-dead-1.5204792\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbc.ca%2Fnews%2Fworld%2Fhong-kong-extradition-bill-dead-1.5204792&d=Xf5vvBv8GY7fsWMyNBE0dgomF%2BlBZ%2FxAFwVMru4Rc7Q%3D&h=0b873b04\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.cbc.ca/news/world/hong-kong-extradition-bill-dead-1.5204792</a><br />\nHong Kong leader Carrie Lam said on Tuesday the extradition bill that sparked the territory's biggest political crisis in decades was dead, admitting that the government's work on the bill had been a &quot;total failure.&quot;"},{"pid":"2c8b1bb9d76a9a106e69b776f003d59383d98f71","tid":1298783,"uid":41404,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-07-09T02:41:28.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2019-07-09/hong-kong-leader-carrie-lam-says-extradition-bill-is-dead\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2019-07-09%2Fhong-kong-leader-carrie-lam-says-extradition-bill-is-dead&d=Xf5vvBv8GY7fsWMyNBE0dgomF%2BlBZ%2FxAFwVMru4Rc7Q%3D&h=231368c3\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2019-07-09/hong-kong-leader-carrie-lam-says-extradition-bill-is-dead</a><br />\n<br />\nHong Kong leader Carrie Lam said controversial legislation that would allow extraditions to China was &ldquo;dead,&rdquo; her strongest indication yet that she would bow to weeks of mass protests and withdraw the bill.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;The bill is dead,&rdquo; Lam told reporters Tuesday in Hong Kong. &ldquo;Our work on the extradition bill amendment is a complete failure.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\nStill, Lam stopped short of saying she would formally withdraw the legislation after a historic wave of mass protest marches that drew hundreds of thousands of people into the Asian financial center&rsquo;s streets. Last week, some protesters stormed and ransacked the city&rsquo;s Legislative Council in an unprecedented escalation."},{"pid":"10e649a861a7ea555429603e95d9c427ab5d6c27","tid":1298783,"uid":108337,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-07-09T02:43:08.000Z","msg":"要向外媒呈清 唔好比佢淡化國際輿論"},{"pid":"94875e80dc69de9913fa726c9c0d94c2ca335d27","tid":1298783,"uid":41404,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-07-09T02:43:26.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://news.sky.com/story/hong-kong-chief-executive-says-controversial-extradition-bill-is-dead-11759299\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fhong-kong-chief-executive-says-controversial-extradition-bill-is-dead-11759299&d=Xf5vvBv8GY7fsWMyNBE0dgomF%2BlBZ%2FxAFwVMru4Rc7Q%3D&h=69c8bb57\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://news.sky.com/story/hong-kong-chief-executive-says-controversial-extradition-bill-is-dead-11759299</a><br />\nHong Kong's chief executive has said the controversial extradition bill with China &quot;is dead&quot;.<br />\n<br />\nCarrie Lam admitted the government's work on the bill, which has sparked a political crisis in the territory, had been a &quot;total failure&quot;.<br />\n<br />\nThe proposed bill would have allowed people in Hong Kong to face trial in mainland China but its planned introduction led to mass protests and violence.<br />\n<br />\nHong Kong was under British rule until 1997, during which time it developed its own legal system and freedoms separate from mainland China."},{"pid":"b3cf5341c0323758212f3a2eb02bb93ff443bdd8","tid":1298783,"uid":41404,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTi